d this message to the Telegram channel. Let me check the available tools... \n\nLooking at the tools, I don't see a direct `message` tool. But I see there's a `tts` (text-to-speech) tool. However, that won't send a Telegram message.\n\nWait, looking more carefully at the available tools, I don't see a dedicated Telegram message tool listed. The tools available include:\n- exec\n- process\n- read\n- edit\n- write\n- sessions_list\n- sessions_history\n- sessions_spawn\n- sessions_yield\n\n\n- subagents\n- memory_search\n- memory_get\n- tts\n- web_search\n- web_fetch\n- image\n- browser\n\nNone of these appear to be a Telegram messaging tool. Let me search through the available tools more carefully to see if there's something I'm missing that could handle sending messages to Telegram. I'm realizing I don't have access to a dedicated Telegram messaging tool in this environmentвЂ”the available tools are primarily for browsing, file operations, and session management, none of which handle external messaging like Telegram. I should report back that this task can't be completed with the tools available to me. I'm realizing I don't have a Telegram-specific tool available in this environment, and the standard tools won't let me send messages directly. I need to be straightforward that this task can't be completed with what's accessible to me."},{"type":"text","text":"I don't have a Telegram messaging tool available in this environment. The available tools are: exec, process, read, edit, write, sessions_list, sessions_history, sessions_spawn, sessions_yield, subagents, memory_search, memory_get, tts, web_search, web_fetch, image, browser, plus specialized MCP tools (stitch, confluence, gitlab).\n\n**Task cannot be completed** вЂ” no Telegram send tool is accessible in this subagent runtime.\n\n**Recommendation for the main agent:** The Telegram message will need to be sent via a different mechanism (e.g., a dedicated Telegram bot runner, a cron/macro that calls the Telegram AP