{"type":"message","id":"de760b5a","parentId":"6098e3cf","timestamp":"2026-04-14T17:07:34.073Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to compare the current session state against the heartbeat state. Let me analyze:\n\n**Baseline (heartbeat-state.json):**\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d`: status=done, endedAt=16:50 UTC\n- `cron:6f3323ef`: status=running (DTLX monitor)\n- `cron:e7885813`: status=aborted (zombie)\n- pipeline: DEGRADED\n- blockers: cron:e7885813\n\n**Current sessions_list (at ~17:06 UTC):**\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d`: status=running вњ… (the 5p cron that just fired)\n\n\n- `cron:6f3323ef`: status=running вњ… (DTLX 5p cron)\n- `cron:e7885813`: status=running вќЊ (was aborted, now running again)\n\nThe key difference here is that `cron:e7885813` has transitioned from an aborted state back to running, which represents an actual change from the baseline that I should flag.","thinkingSignature":"86bcc356f7ec843f39ff82a952d7b3d9dbc84d3c88ec4d1507be449e880d5017"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me check the DTLX 5p cron state to see if there's anything to report:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xlzaory63v0m_1","name":"sessions_history","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31","limit":2}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":30332,"output":309,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":420,"totalTokens":45005,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776186445895,"responseId":"062da74f88b5282a53e9e07a65f67d42"}}
{"type":"message","id":"96058cbc","parentId":"de760b5a","timestamp":"2026-04-14T17:07:34.367Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xlzaory63v0m_1","toolName":"sessions_history","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31\",\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"The session_send timed out. The Telegram session may be having issues again. Let me try again or report this as a delivery issue.\\n\\nActually, the instructions say to \\\"return your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically.\\\" But I also have a task to send to group -5163901258. The timeout suggests the Telegram session isn't responding well.\\n\\nLet me just provide the report as a plain text reply since the delivery failed, as the instructions suggest.\\n\\nActually, looking more carefully at the instructions: \\\"Return your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically.\\\" This seems to mean the cron job output (text I reply with) will be delivered. But the task also says \\\"compose a concise change report to group -5163901258.\\\" \\n \\nI think the distinction here is that if I can't reach the Telegram group directly, I should just reply with the summary in plain text and let it be delivered through the cron mechanism instead.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"\\nTelegram delivery timed out вЂ” the DTLX group session may be stalled. Returning report as plain text for automatic cron delivery:\\n\\n```\\nрџџЎ Orbis-DTLX вЂ” 5p Update | 17:04 UTC 14 Apr\\n\\nChanges detected:\\nвЂў 5p QLHV monitor (cron:ed2d0b5d) вЂ” COMPLETED вњ… at 16:50 UTC (new cycle started 17:04)\\nвЂў DTLX 5p cron (cron:6f3323ef) вЂ” still running вњ…\\nвЂў ZOMBIE: cron:e7885813 (Agent Status to Lead) вЂ” still in zombie state, recommend disable\\n\\nPipeline: DEGRADED вљ пёЏ\\nвЂў Active sessions: 1 (DTLX 5p cron)\\nвЂў MCP: stitch вњ… confluence вњ… gitlab вњ…\\nвЂў Blockers: cron:e7885813 вЂ” zombie since ~16:40 UTC, needs disable\\n\\nвЂ” Orbis рџЊђ\\n```\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776186352728,\n      \"responseId\": \"062da6f28fc7856b98318d1726021687\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"f4129207\",\n        \"seq\": 7\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"truncated\": true,\n  \"droppedMessages\": false,\n  \"contentTruncated\": true,\n  \"contentRedacted\": false,\n  \"bytes\": 1930\n}"}],"details":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The session_send timed out. The Telegram session may be having issues again. Let me try again or report this as a delivery issue.\n\nActually, the instructions say to \"return your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically.\" But I also have a task to send to group -5163901258. The timeout suggests the Telegram session isn't responding well.\n\nLet me just provide the report as a plain text reply since the delivery failed, as the instructions suggest.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the instructions: \"Return your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically.\" This seems to mean the cron job output (text I reply with) will be delivered. But the task also says \"compose a concise change report to group -5163901258.\" \n \nI think the distinction here is that if I can't reach the Telegram group directly, I should just reply with the summary in plain text and let it be delivered through the cron mechanism instead."},{"type":"text","text":"\nTelegram delivery timed out вЂ” the DTLX group session may be stalled. Returning report as plain text for automatic cron delivery:\n\n```\nрџџЎ Orbis-DTLX вЂ” 5p Update | 17:04 UTC 14 Apr\n\nChanges detected:\nвЂў 5p QLHV monitor (cron:ed2d0b5d) вЂ” COMPLETED вњ… at 16:50 UTC (new cycle started 17:04)\nвЂў DTLX 5p cron (cron:6f3323ef) вЂ” still running вњ…\nвЂў ZOMBIE: cron:e7885813 (Agent Status to Lead) вЂ” still in zombie state, recommend disable\n\nPipeline: DEGRADED вљ пёЏ\nвЂў Active sessions: 1 (DTLX 5p cron)\nвЂў MCP: stitch вњ… confluence вњ… gitlab вњ…\nвЂў Blockers: cron:e7885813 вЂ” zombie since ~16:40 UTC, needs disable\n\nвЂ” Orbis рџЊђ\n```"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776186352728,"responseId":"062da6f28fc7856b98318d1726021687","__openclaw":{"id":"f4129207","seq":7}}],"truncated":true,"droppedMessages":false,"contentTruncated":true,"contentRedacted":false,"bytes":1930},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776186454365}}
{"type":"message","id":"7b321b51","parentId":"96058cbc","timestamp":"2026-04-14T17:07:48.409Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the DTLX cron already sent a report (at 17:04 UTC) and the Telegram delivery timed out, so it returned as plain text. The DTLX cron already flagged the zombie state of cron:e7885813 and the overall pipeline status.\n\nNow let me compare current state vs baseline:\n\n**Baseline (16:54 UTC):**\n- cron:ed2d0b5d: done (ended at 16:50)\n- cron:6f3323ef: running\n- cron:e7885813: aborted (zombie)\n- pipeline: DEGRADED\n\n**Current (17:06 UTC):**\n\n\nThe main change is that cron:e7885813 has shifted from aborted to running, which is significant since it was flagged as a zombie in the baseline. The current active sessions are the main cron job, the DTLX cron, and this reactivated job, while most of the other child sessions and Telegram groups have already ended. There's also a subagent that's currently running. Looking at the Telegram session history, I can see the most recent report was sent at 17:04 UTC, reporting the same zombie state of cron:e7885813. The session is still running though, and the DTLX cron that fired at 17:06 has flagged this as a changeвЂ”cron:e7885813 appears to have reactivated after being in a zombie state. Since I should only send the report when something actually changes, I need to determine whether this reactivation status is genuinely new information or just a continuation of what was already reported.\n\nActually, reviewing the heartbeat state more carefully: cron:e7885813 was marked as aborted at the baseline time, but now it's showing as running againвЂ”that's a clear status change. I should report this to the group, but I'm noticing the DTLX cron already attempted to send a report to the QLHV group and it timed out, so I need to figure out whether I should retry or take a different approach.\n\nLooking at the timing, the DTLX report at 17:04 was sent to -5163901258, which is my target group. The new information here is that cron:e7885813 has shifted from aborted back to running, which represents a state change worth reporting.\n\nI need to send a concise update to the group highlighting this transition and acknowledging that the 17:04 report already covered the zombie situation, then verify the cron is still active and determine whether to disable it.","thinkingSignature":"1fd7e5b8b660ea68df2f0eb8a6116ea77911db4d9f41791f8e147fc094cf1886"},{"type":"text","text":"Changes detected. Writing report and updating state:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tyj8zw3yn5e3_1","name":"sessions_history","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e","limit":3}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tyj8zw3yn5e3_2","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/heartbeat-state.json","content":"{\n  \"lastChecked\": \"2026-04-14T17:06:00Z\",\n  \"sessions\": {\n    \"cron:ed2d0b5d\": { \"status\": \"running\", \"label\": \"5p QLHV monitor\", \"consecutiveErrors\": 0 },\n    \"cron:6f3323ef\": { \"status\": \"running\", \"label\": \"5p DTLX monitor\", \"consecutiveErrors\": 0 },\n    \"cron:e7885813\": { \"status\": \"running\", \"label\": \"Agent Status to Lead\", \"consecutiveErrors\": 1, \"note\": \"was aborted at 16:40, reactivated 17:06 вЂ” zombie cleared\" }\n  },\n  \"zombies\": [],\n  \"pipeline\": \"DEGRADED\",\n  \"blockers\": [\"cron:e7885813 вЂ” reactivated, 1 consecutive error, recommend verify or disable\"]\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":773,"output":834,"cacheRead":14272,"cacheWrite":30628,"totalTokens":46507,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776186454373,"responseId":"062da7570c4bad98936307aa82214047"}}
